## Backend-Specific Rules

### API Design
- Follow RESTful conventions (or your project's chosen API style)
- Version APIs appropriately
- Document all endpoints in `docs/api.md`
- Use consistent error response format

### Database
- Always use migrations for schema changes (never manual DDL)
- Use parameterized queries (no string concatenation)
- Index foreign keys and frequently queried columns
- Document schema changes in migration files

### Security
- Validate all inputs at the controller layer
- Use parameterized queries for all database access
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
- Apply rate limiting to public endpoints
- Follow the security checklist in the orchestrator repo

### Testing
- Unit tests for all service-layer functions
- Integration tests for API endpoints
- Test both success and error paths
- Mock external services in tests

